  "metadata": {
    "modules": [
      {
        "name": "BrowserEngineKit"
      }
    ],
    "role": "article",
    "roleHeading": "Article",
    "title": "Attributing memory to a content extension"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A web browserâ€™s GPU extension is limited to a small total memory allocation.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "To allocate large amounts of memory in a GPU extension on behalf of a content extension, attribute the memory to that content extension.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The GPU and the content extension both need specific memory transfer entitlements to participate in memory attribution.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "In the content extension, you create a token that identifies the extension to the kernel.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Pass the token to the GPU using your interprocess communication (IPC) channel.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Then, in the GPU extension, use the token to assign ownership of the memory region to the content process.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Use-the-correct-entitlements",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Use the correct entitlements",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To participate in memory attribution, your content extension needs both the web-browser content extension entitlement ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "com.apple.developer.web-browser-engine.webcontent",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " and the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "com.apple.developer.memory.transfer_accept",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " entitlement.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Your GPU extension needs both the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "com.apple.developer.web-browser-engine.rendering",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "com.apple.developer.memory.transfer_send",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " entitlements.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Set the value for each of these entitlements to a string that matches the bundle ID of your browser app.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For more information about the entitlements web browser extensions use, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.BrowserEngineKit/documentation/BrowserEngineKit/designing-your-browser-architecture",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Create-a-task-identity-token",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Create a task identity token",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Your content extension creates a task identity token that you pass to the GPU extension using your IPC protocol, for example, with ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/XPC",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "The task identity token is an unforgeable value that the operating system uses to identify the process to which it attributes memory in the GPU extension.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To create a task identity token:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "task_id_token_t identityToken;",
            "mach_port_t port = mach_task_self();",
            "kern_result_t result = task_create_identity_token(port, &identityToken);",
            "",
            "if (result == KERN_SUCCESS) {",
            "  // Send identityToken to the GPU extension.",
            "} else {",
            "  // Handle the error.",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "c",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Attribute-memory-to-the-content-extension",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Attribute memory to the content extension",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Receive the task identity token in the GPU extension and use it to attribute memory to the content extension.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To attribute an ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/IOSurface/IOSurfaceRef",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to a content extension, call ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "IOSurfaceSetOwnershipIdentity",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ":",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "IOSurfaceRef surface = /* Create an IOSurface. */;",
            "task_id_token_t identityToken = /* Receive the token using your IPC channel. */;",
            "kern_return_t result = IOSurfaceSetOwnershipIdentity(surface,",
            "\tidentityToken,",
            "\tkIOSurfaceMemoryLedgerTagGraphics,",
            "\t0);",
            "",
            "if (result != KERN_SUCCESS) {",
            "  // Handle the error.",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "c",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To attribute a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "MTLResource",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " to a content extension, send it a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "setOwnerWithIdentity:",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " message:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "MTLResource *resource = /* Create a resource. */;",
            "task_id_token_t identityToken = /* Receive the token using your IPC channel. */;",
            "kern_return_t result = [resource setOwnerWithIdentity: identityToken];",
            "",
            "if (result != KERN_SUCCESS) {",
            "  // Handle the error.",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "objc",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Free-the-memory-when-the-content-extension-finishes",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Free the memory when the content extension finishes",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When the content extension exits, whether normally or due to an error, free the memory thatâ€™s attributed to it in your GPU extension.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If you use ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "libxpc",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " to implement your IPC protocol, use the connectionâ€™s invalidation handler to detect when the content extension exits.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
